          <mj-image width="52px" src="https://harrydry.s3.amazonaws.com/gdmarketing/email/meLogo1.png" alt="Marketing Examples Logo" padding-top="9px" href="https://marketingexamples.com"></mj-image>
          <mj-text mj-class="h1" align="center">#003 - Revue's Newsletter Sign Up Flow</mj-text>
          <mj-text mj-class="p">Over the last couple of days I've been signing up to other companies newsletters in search of a lovely newsletter sign-up flow to copy from. Revue's is the best I've found yet. Let's take a look:</mj-text>
          <mj-text mj-class="h2">The TLDR</mj-text>
          <mj-text mj-class="p list list__top">&#x2022; Confirmation email on sign-up</mj-text>
          <mj-text mj-class="p list list__bottom">&#x2022; Reminder to check spam (preventing initial email getting lost)</mj-text>
          <mj-image mj-class="cImg img400" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/revue1.png" alt="Trennd Reddit Promotion"></mj-image>
          <mj-text mj-class="p list list__top">&#x2022; Ask recipient to add to address book. This is the <span class="bold">only</span> foolproof way of guarantying your email gets delivered.</mj-text>
          <mj-image mj-class="cImg img400" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/revue2.png" alt="Trennd Reddit Promotion"></mj-image>
          <mj-text mj-class="h2">DOES IT WORK?</mj-text>
          <mj-text mj-class="p">Inspired by Revueâ€™s example I devised a new welcome flow for Marketing Examples. And I've compared the before / after results in the full article.</mj-text>
        </mj-column>
